      <hedline>
        <hl1>EMBRAER EXPANDING PRODUCTION</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazilian aircraft maker Embraer, in effort to increase exports of civilian and military airplanes, will invest $189 million to build new plant and aerospace research center in state of Sao Paulo; factory will be operating in September 2001; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In an effort to increase exports of civilian and military airplanes, the Brazilian aircraft maker Embraer will invest $189 million to build a new plant and aerospace research center in the state of Sao Paulo. The plant will be used to assemble regional jets and upgrade military aircraft. The factory, Embraer's third, will begin operating in September 2001.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
